In addition to J.B.&#39;s good advice, I typically have an Ant task to run
the tests with the JVM property necessary to find the root directory.
Here&#39;s an example for those interested:

    &lt;target name=&quot;test&quot; depends=&quot;compile.tests&quot; if=&quot;junit.present&quot;&gt;
        &lt;junit fork=&quot;yes&quot; printsummary=&quot;no&quot; haltonfailure=&quot;yes&quot;&gt;
            &lt;jvmarg value=&quot;-Dtest.data.dir=${test.data.dir}&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;classpath refid=&quot;project.classpath&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;formatter type=&quot;plain&quot; usefile=&quot;false&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;test name=&quot;${main.test}&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/junit&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;

